article.headline: Austin Peay 89, Tennessee State 44
article.story: CLARKSVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Derek Wright hit every shot for 16 points as Austin Peay beat Tennessee State 89-44 Monday night, clinching the No. 1 seed in the Ohio Valley Conference tournament. The Governors (18-7, 15-2 OVC) shot 63.8 percent from the field in winning their 15th game in the last 16 starts. Wright hit all five field goals, including his two 3-pointers, and was 4-of-4 from the free throw line. Drake Reed added 15 points and six rebounds for Austin Peay, hitting 6-of-8 from the field. Wes Channels added 14 points and J.P. Felder had 10. Tennessee State (10-17, 6-11) had just one player in double figures, Andrae Belton with 16 and a team-high nine rebounds. The loss was the seventh straight for Tennessee State, which is just 2-13 on the road this season. The Tigers shot just 23 percent and were only 2-of-27 from 3-point range. Austin Peay led nearly all the game, jumping out to a 23-12 lead with 9:50 left in the first half. It was 38-20 at the half.
